President Biden has announced that John Kirby will be the new National Security Council Coordinator for Strategic Communications at the White House. In this role, Kirby will coordinate efforts to explain US policy and serve as a senior administration voice on related matters. Kirby, who currently serves as the Assistant to the Secretary of Defense for Public Affairs, has a strong background in foreign and defense policy. He has previously served as the Assistant Secretary for the Bureau of Public Affairs at the State Department and as the Pentagon Press Secretary. Kirby is a retired Rear Admiral in the US Navy and holds degrees in International Relations and National Security and Strategic Studies.